qa: how do chameleons change their color

qa: what is quick sort algorithm
ans: Quick sort is fast, in place , unstable.In Quick sort you  select a random element (There are different strategies to select Pivot) as Pivot, then you move all the element greater than the pivot to its right and less than the pivot to its left. qu: why is the complexity of bfs not o v e
qa: why is the time complexity of bfs o v e
ans: Bfs starts with an arbitrary vertex. Each neighboring vertex is inserted once into a queue. This is done by looking at the edges of the vertex. Each visited vertex is marked so it cannot be visited again: each vertex is visited exactly once, and all edges of each vertex are checked. So the runtime is V+E.Note that this assumes one connected component of the graph.

qu: what is the probability of someone winning the lottery if there are an infinite number of contestants
qa: what is the probability of someone winning the lottery if there are infinite contestants
ans: Assuming that each of the infinite number of players bought one ticket and assuming you also bought one ticket, if the lottery was Powerball, then your chance of winning are still 1 in ~292 million. So it is extremely unlikely that you would win, but if you did happen to win, then your prize would be zero because it would be divided among an infinite number of other jackpot winners.

qu: how much does 5 gallons of water weigh
qa: how many lbs does 5 8 gallons of gasoline weigh
ans: There are 3.7841 liters in one gallon. One liter of water would weigh 1000 grams. The specific gravity of gasoline is about 0.82. Thus the weight of one gallon of gasoline is about 3.7841 x 1000x0.82 = 3102.96 grams or about 3 kilograms.

qu: what is shearings
qa: what is shear loading
ans: A shear load is a force that causes shear stress when applied to a structural element. Shear stress, which is a force per unit area, occurs in the plane perpendicular to normal stress; it is created when two planes of the same object are trying to slide past one another. Engineers need to calculate the shear load on structures to make sure they don't experience mechanical failure.

qu: why are speedometers inaccurate
qa: what is the working mechanism in a speedometer in automobiles
ans: Older cars had what was called a speedometer cable. It was connected to a coil in the transmission and as the car moved faster it pulled on the cable, making the speed go up. Modern cars have what's called a Vehicle Speed Sensor that plugs into the transmission and then this signal goes to the vehicle's computer which then outputs a signal to the speedometer.

R is a constant that is generally .0821.So, at STP, your pressure is 1 atm, the temperature is 25 degrees Celsius, or 298 Kelvin, which is what the equation works in. qa: why are the deserts located in the tropical zones and in the western margins of the continents
ans: Most of the worlds deserts found on the western margins of continents in the subtropics because the prevailing winds in the tropics are tropical easterly winds. The tropical easterly winds become dry by the time they reach the western margins of the continents and so they bring no rainfall. Thus, the region becomes devoid of moisture which causes dry conditions leading to formation of deserts.
